Field Label: Record ID
Did you have any of the following problems during your most recent pregnancy? For each item, choose Yes if you had the problem or choose No if you did not.
Did you have any of the following problems during your most recent pregnancy? - Vaginal bleeding
Did you have any of the following problems during your most recent pregnancy? - Kidney or bladder (urinary tract) infection
Did you have any of the following problems during your most recent pregnancy? - Severe nausea, vomiting, or dehydration
Did you have any of the following problems during your most recent pregnancy? - Cervix had to be sewn shut (cerclage for incompetent cervix)
Did you have any of the following problems during your most recent pregnancy? - High blood pressure, hypertension (including pregnancy-induced hypertension [PIH]), preeclampsia, or toxemia
Did you have any of the following problems during your most recent pregnancy? - Problems with the placenta (such as abruptio placentae or placenta previa)
Did you have any of the following problems during your most recent pregnancy? - Labor pains more than 3 weeks before my baby was due (preterm or early labor)
Did you have any of the following problems during your most recent pregnancy? - Water broke more than 3 weeks before my baby was due (premature rupture of membranes [PROM])
Did you have any of the following problems during your most recent pregnancy? - I had to have a blood transfusion
Did you have any of the following problems during your most recent pregnancy? - I was hurt in a car accident
The next questions are about the time since your new baby was born.
After your baby was born, was he or she put in an intensive care unit?
After your baby was born, how long did he or she stay in the hospital?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Less than 24 hours (less than 1 day) | 2, 24 to 48 hours (1 to 2 days) | 3, 3 to 5 days | 4, 6 to 14 days | 5, More than 14 days | 6, My baby was not born in a hospital | 7, My baby is still in the hospital
